(Awkward)

241
00:15:40,166 --> 00:15:41,916
(Seo Jae-hyung)

242
00:15:41,941 --> 00:15:43,265
Look at his expression. Wow.

243
00:15:45,317 --> 00:15:47,898
- He's extravagant.
- Indeed.

244
00:15:50,195 --> 00:15:51,433
(Glance)

245
00:15:52,044 --> 00:15:54,809
- You must like accessories.
- Oh, me?

246
00:15:58,746 --> 00:15:59,999
- I do.
- Really?

247
00:16:00,024 --> 00:16:01,024
Yes.

248
00:16:01,114 --> 00:16:02,358
That's a nice bracelet.

249
00:16:04,732 --> 00:16:06,313
Thanks.

250
00:16:07,572 --> 00:16:12,128
We all saw each others'
profiles. Can you tell who's who?

251
00:16:16,200 --> 00:16:17,938
- I can.
- You can?

252
00:16:18,224 --> 00:16:19,757
- Yup.
- Wow, already?

253
00:16:20,197 --> 00:16:21,197
I think so, too.

254
00:16:22,014 --> 00:16:24,206
- I'm so curious.
- I know. Can you tell?

255
00:16:25,313 --> 00:16:27,345
- I have no idea.
- Right? Same here.

256
00:16:28,937 --> 00:16:33,143
When I get to know someone,
I keep an eye on them.

257
00:16:33,426 --> 00:16:39,957
Once I like someone,
that's when it all begins.

258
00:16:40,893 --> 00:16:42,544
How many participants are there?

259
00:16:43,060 --> 00:16:46,094
- I think there are 10 people.
- Five men and five women?

260
00:16:47,250 --> 00:16:49,797
- Are there enough chairs?
- Oh, are there?

261
00:16:49,822 --> 00:16:51,003
There are nine chairs.

262
00:16:52,627 --> 00:16:54,484
How many profile cards were there...?

263
00:16:54,881 --> 00:16:57,717
- I don't remember.
- There are five guys, right?

264
00:16:59,540 --> 00:17:02,407
- That's why there are nine chairs.
- Oh, there are only four girls?

265
00:17:02,763 --> 00:17:03,763
Yes.

266
00:17:06,674 --> 00:17:07,941
It's an odd number.

267
00:17:09,039 --> 00:17:13,517
(The numbers of men and
women don't match up?)

268
00:17:19,191 --> 00:17:23,410
(The sixth participant hurries along.)

269
00:17:31,499 --> 00:17:33,375
(Please pick your identity.)

270
00:17:34,029 --> 00:17:36,394
That's right. They need to choose first.

271
00:17:36,690 --> 00:17:38,166
Is it money or love?

272
00:17:38,191 --> 00:17:43,430
(Money catchers may
fabricate their identities.)

273
00:17:43,538 --> 00:17:44,808
No way!

274
00:17:45,079 --> 00:17:47,467
This is something new
in this season, right?

275
00:17:47,875 --> 00:17:52,115
- They changed it.
- They start with lies then.

276
00:17:52,140 --> 00:17:55,373
That means your profile is a lie.

277
00:17:55,647 --> 00:17:59,307
- You can lie or not lie.
- Yes.

278
00:17:59,365 --> 00:18:01,143
Money Catchers can choose.

279
00:18:01,168 --> 00:18:04,397
- Gosh, this is fun!
- This is getting interesting!

280
00:18:04,422 --> 00:18:06,323
I feel like at the end,
someone will be like...

281
00:18:09,786 --> 00:18:10,786
I'm excited!

282
00:18:11,984 --> 00:18:15,546
(She's hesitating which one to choose. Is
she a Love Catcher or a Money Catcher?)

283
00:18:15,584 --> 00:18:17,771
(Will you choose LOVE?
Will you choose MONEY?)

284
00:18:22,493 --> 00:18:27,590
- Hello.
- Hello.

285
00:18:28,933 --> 00:18:30,665
- She's cute.
- She looks young.

286
00:18:31,232 --> 00:18:32,366
What's your name?

287
00:18:32,677 --> 00:18:34,844
My name is Yang Ji-min.

288
00:18:36,698 --> 00:18:38,498
Oh, we can't say anything else.

289
00:18:38,809 --> 00:18:39,809
Right.

290
00:18:41,330 --> 00:18:43,479
(Clue: Baby-faced. Is she
here for love or money?)

291
00:18:43,504 --> 00:18:47,723
I totally want to get married.
It's been my dream ever since I was little.

292
00:18:47,748 --> 00:18:51,281
I want a husband who's
sweet, polite, and loves kids.

293
00:18:51,582 --> 00:18:55,803
But my dad said that's childish. He said
no one gets married before 30 these days.

294
00:18:56,998 --> 00:18:59,704
I guess we have to go in order.
Do you have good memory?

295
00:18:59,729 --> 00:19:01,934
- Yes.
- I'm Jung Su-won.

296
00:19:02,299 --> 00:19:03,748
I'm Ahn Ji-min.

297
00:19:04,037 --> 00:19:05,822
- You two have the same name.
- Oh, I see.

298
00:19:06,418 --> 00:19:09,085
- I'm Seo Jae-hyung.
- I'm Lee Ha-neul.

299
00:19:09,470 --> 00:19:10,915
I'm Lee In-seong.

300
00:19:11,617 --> 00:19:13,918
Did you remember everything?
I'm gonna quiz you.

301
00:19:15,080 --> 00:19:16,786
I don't think I remember all the names.

302
00:19:17,003 --> 00:19:19,736
- Isn't my name easy to remember?
- Yes.

303
00:19:20,133 --> 00:19:22,069
I remembered everyone's names but his.

304
00:19:22,094 --> 00:19:23,166
Except for mine?

305
00:19:26,687 --> 00:19:28,823
(The seventh participant)

306
00:19:28,848 --> 00:19:31,467
I just want to show who I am.

307
00:19:32,249 --> 00:19:34,693
I think I'm honest.

308
00:19:35,150 --> 00:19:39,547
I don't like putting on a
facade, so I just act comfortably.

309
00:19:42,761 --> 00:19:44,744
- Oh, hi.
- Hello.

310
00:19:46,007 --> 00:19:49,040
(Yoon Jung-woo)

311
00:19:49,276 --> 00:19:51,165
- Hello.
- Hi.

312
00:19:52,363 --> 00:19:54,934
(Where will Jung-woo sit?)

313
00:19:56,171 --> 00:19:58,130
(An empty seat between
Ha-neul and In-seong)

314
00:19:58,670 --> 00:20:00,761
- May I sit here?
- Sure, go ahead.

315
00:20:02,343 --> 00:20:05,470
It could be a bit burdensome
to sit between two women.

316
00:20:09,414 --> 00:20:11,614
He could be the introverted type.

317
00:20:13,449 --> 00:20:17,750
I learn face-reading, so I see
people from a different perspective.

318
00:20:18,161 --> 00:20:22,448
I like women with round
faces with pretty cheekbones.

319
00:20:23,978 --> 00:20:28,169
(Is there someone who caught his
eye out of the women with pretty smiles?)

320
00:20:28,783 --> 00:20:31,585
If they have big cheekbones, you
can see their smiles more clearly.

321
00:20:31,610 --> 00:20:33,414
It feels like they're smiling brightly.

322
00:20:37,970 --> 00:20:40,644
(The eighth participant)

323
00:20:44,818 --> 00:20:49,247
(He fixes his hair and adjusts
his clothes as if he's nervous.)

324
00:20:57,766 --> 00:20:58,766
(Surprised)

325
00:20:59,218 --> 00:21:03,506
- Hello.
- Hi.

326
00:21:07,617 --> 00:21:11,721
(Won-jae sits between
In-seong and Ha-neul.)

327
00:21:12,472 --> 00:21:13,472
(Glance)

328
00:21:14,344 --> 00:21:17,841
Why do you seem familiar? Am I mistake?
Why does it feel like I've seen you before?

329
00:21:22,183 --> 00:21:23,183
I'm not sure.

330
00:21:24,606 --> 00:21:27,272
Currently, I'm studying physical
education at Inha University.

331
00:21:27,297 --> 00:21:29,809
I'm Kang Won-jae, who is
training in physical education which

332
00:21:29,834 --> 00:21:32,427
you can only get in if you
trained in military and martial arts.

333
00:21:32,452 --> 00:21:33,519
Kang Won-jae...?

334
00:21:33,544 --> 00:21:36,630
Oh, he's from "Steel Troops!"

335
00:21:37,596 --> 00:21:38,596
The army!

336
00:21:38,621 --> 00:21:40,112
- Oh, right.
- SDT.

337
00:21:40,629 --> 00:21:42,819
No wonder his suit looked so tight!

338
00:21:45,969 --> 00:21:47,691
Ha-neul recognized him right away.

339
00:21:50,243 --> 00:21:52,505
(The ninth participant is
walking with excited steps.)

340
00:21:52,530 --> 00:21:54,434
- She's the last one.
- The last one.

341
00:21:56,028 --> 00:21:59,352
I think I'll give a
strong first impression.

342
00:22:02,477 --> 00:22:06,193
I'm not someone who's in the shadows,

343
00:22:06,218 --> 00:22:08,800
so I think I'll grab attention
during the first encounter.

344
00:22:10,051 --> 00:22:13,868
Hello. Hello. Hello.

345
00:22:14,268 --> 00:22:16,467
- Where should I sit?
- He's suddenly leaning forward.

346
00:22:16,951 --> 00:22:18,316
(All eyes on her.)

347
00:22:20,091 --> 00:22:24,281
(Lee Yeo-min)

348
00:22:24,306 --> 00:22:26,692
- Is she from a beauty pageant?
- She's beautiful.

349
00:22:28,609 --> 00:22:31,482
- Is she the last one?
- Yes, I think so.

350
00:22:32,138 --> 00:22:35,852
But when I came in here, they gave me this.

351
00:22:38,151 --> 00:22:39,698
- Hello.
- Hi.

352
00:22:40,892 --> 00:22:43,653
- Should I take this?
- You can read it in there.

353
00:22:44,540 --> 00:22:45,540
What's that?

354
00:22:47,923 --> 00:22:50,837
- Could you read it?
- Should I read it out loud?

355
00:22:53,730 --> 00:22:54,730
(Curious)

356
00:22:55,294 --> 00:22:58,250
Tomorrow, come to the
lodging with the one you like.

357
00:22:58,634 --> 00:23:00,753
We can freely start talking now.

358
00:23:01,549 --> 00:23:04,398
- Tomorrow?
- So they're just meeting today?

359
00:23:04,423 --> 00:23:07,568
- With the one they like?
- I guess they're not going there now.

360
00:23:07,593 --> 00:23:09,096
Tomorrow?

361
00:23:09,779 --> 00:23:12,082
The men are going to
pick up the women, right?

362
00:23:12,107 --> 00:23:15,989
Right. He'll escort her, and
they'll go to the lodging together.

363
00:23:16,474 --> 00:23:21,018
(Silence fills the bar after
the mission card is read.)

364
00:23:21,855 --> 00:23:22,855
(Worried)

365
00:23:23,831 --> 00:23:27,239
Honestly, I was very flustered.

366
00:23:27,751 --> 00:23:30,625
There are four women and five men.

367
00:23:31,288 --> 00:23:35,176
One person will have to go there alone.

368
00:23:35,983 --> 00:23:38,459
I realized I could end up going by myself.

369
00:23:38,740 --> 00:23:45,009
I'm worried that no one will
come pick me up tomorrow.

370
00:23:46,375 --> 00:23:49,343
(The first meeting is filled with
strange excitement and worry.)

371
00:23:50,180 --> 00:23:52,338
- Did you all eat?
- It looks so good.

372
00:23:52,632 --> 00:23:55,759
- I'm starving.
- It looks delicious.

373
00:23:58,729 --> 00:24:01,197
- They're too pretty to eat.
- Absolutely.

374
00:24:01,636 --> 00:24:03,414
I have no idea what I should eat.

375
00:24:05,438 --> 00:24:07,306
Oh, this looks
good. I pick this one.

376
00:24:07,667 --> 00:24:10,119
(They pick the foods they want.)

377
00:24:11,297 --> 00:24:13,971
The seats are too... separated.

378
00:24:16,733 --> 00:24:18,558
- Everyone is...
- They're all anxious.

379
00:24:18,583 --> 00:24:20,018
They can't eat.

380
00:24:20,919 --> 00:24:24,858
If you like someone, do you sit
next to them or across from them?

381
00:24:24,883 --> 00:24:28,091
Right now, shouldn't they sit across from
each other? So they can see each other?

382
00:24:28,116 --> 00:24:32,404
I heard that it's better
to sit next to each other.

383
00:24:32,429 --> 00:24:34,822
They say that you
should sit at the left side.

384
00:24:34,847 --> 00:24:39,803
That's near their heart, and you
should whisper in their left ear.

385
00:24:39,828 --> 00:24:41,366
That's what they say.

386
00:24:41,391 --> 00:24:42,798
Oh, I see.

387
00:24:45,400 --> 00:24:46,765
I think this is meatball.

388
00:24:48,470 --> 00:24:51,165
(Ha-neul doesn't feel Su-won's
gaze and focuses on the food.)

389
00:24:51,190 --> 00:24:52,466
Ha-neul?

390
00:24:57,884 --> 00:25:02,492
(Su-won naturally moves near Ha-neul.)

391
00:25:03,061 --> 00:25:08,334
Su-won already got his food, but it seemed
like he was waiting for her to find a seat.

392
00:25:09,941 --> 00:25:12,195
- What's that?
- I'm not sure.

393
00:25:15,393 --> 00:25:17,653
(There's something
subtle flowing between

394
00:25:17,678 --> 00:25:20,152
them as they get to
know each other's tastes.)

395
00:25:25,479 --> 00:25:26,947
He sat down first.

396
00:25:29,127 --> 00:25:31,233
It could be because he's confident.

397
00:25:34,077 --> 00:25:35,450
It's nerve-racking.

398
00:25:35,475 --> 00:25:36,918
(Glance)

399
00:25:42,136 --> 00:25:45,151
(With Su-won being the last one to
take a seat, all the men are at a table.)

400
00:25:46,701 --> 00:25:48,113
Where do I have to sit?

401
00:25:48,647 --> 00:25:49,908
It's really...

402
00:25:54,112 --> 00:25:56,352
Who will muster up the courage first?

403
00:25:57,094 --> 00:26:01,459
- Could this be seen as their choice?
- Yup.

404
00:26:01,484 --> 00:26:03,843
(Who will be the brave
one to approach first?)

405
00:26:04,212 --> 00:26:05,814
Should we sit here?

406
00:26:06,288 --> 00:26:09,812
- Hello.
- Hello.

407
00:26:12,599 --> 00:26:13,932
- Hello.
- Hello.

408
00:26:14,926 --> 00:26:19,197
(Are Ji-min and In-seong
interested in Jung-woo?)

409
00:26:20,164 --> 00:26:22,710
(Yeo-min and Ha-neul haven't decided yet.)

410
00:26:22,735 --> 00:26:24,046
I'll go over there.

411
00:26:26,030 --> 00:26:27,935
- Hello.
- Hi.

412
00:26:29,411 --> 00:26:31,133
You didn't bring a lot of food.

413
00:26:31,426 --> 00:26:34,516
I want to try some
before getting some more.

414
00:26:35,376 --> 00:26:37,109
Yeo-min is an expert in this.

415
00:26:37,729 --> 00:26:38,934
You have a dialect.

416
00:26:38,968 --> 00:26:41,713
- I'm from Busan.
- Busan? I'm from Gyeongsang-do.

417
00:26:41,738 --> 00:26:47,117
- Do you know Masan?
- I work there...

418
00:26:47,621 --> 00:26:49,887
Where should I go?
I'll sit here.

419
00:26:49,912 --> 00:26:52,988
(Ha-neul is still standing,
and Su-won is watching her.)

420
00:26:53,013 --> 00:26:54,613
He keeps looking at her.

421
00:26:55,522 --> 00:26:59,827
(Ha-neul sits with Won-jae and Ji-min.)

422
00:27:03,375 --> 00:27:07,097
- Su-won seems interested in her, right?
- It's love at first sight.

423
00:27:08,397 --> 00:27:12,247
At this rate, he'll spill all his food.

424
00:27:19,089 --> 00:27:22,145
- What's going on?
- He's by himself!

425
00:27:23,024 --> 00:27:27,380
- Jae-hyung is...
- He's Mr. Popular though!

426
00:27:28,233 --> 00:27:29,868
This is bad!

427
00:27:29,893 --> 00:27:33,555
(Unlike the others who are chatting
together, he's quietly eating alone.)

428
00:27:33,875 --> 00:27:36,447
How do I put it? I'm observing.

429
00:27:37,157 --> 00:27:42,387
When I get to learn
something, I tend to watch them.

430
00:27:42,583 --> 00:27:47,908
I approach someone once
I get interested in them.

431
00:27:48,479 --> 00:27:51,272
I'm confident, but this is how I am.

432
00:27:52,613 --> 00:27:54,386
Everything's going according to plan.

433
00:27:56,898 --> 00:27:58,970
- So that's his plan.
- It's going smoothly.

434
00:28:00,721 --> 00:28:02,007
(She spots Jae-hyung.)

435
00:28:02,032 --> 00:28:03,419
He's eating by himself.

436
00:28:04,651 --> 00:28:06,756
- Should I tell him to join us?
- What?

437
00:28:06,847 --> 00:28:07,847
Oh, sure.

438
00:28:08,166 --> 00:28:11,833
- Jae-hyung, would you like to join us?
- Eat with us.

439
00:28:14,147 --> 00:28:15,380
(Hesitating)

440
00:28:15,785 --> 00:28:17,467
- Should I?
- yes.

441
00:28:17,731 --> 00:28:20,310
- Eat with us.
- Come here.

442
00:28:22,061 --> 00:28:23,061
He went.

443
00:28:24,047 --> 00:28:25,833
I brought the most food.

444
00:28:25,858 --> 00:28:27,428
Did you already eat?

445
00:28:27,852 --> 00:28:29,567
I did, but it's been a while.

446
00:28:30,129 --> 00:28:33,523
I think it'd be nice if
you become less shy.

447
00:28:33,548 --> 00:28:37,081
- I'm shy around strangers, too.
- I'm really timid.

448
00:28:38,015 --> 00:28:40,261
- Same here.
- Me, too.

449
00:28:40,286 --> 00:28:42,381
- I'm shy, too.
- Is everyone here timid?

450
00:28:42,406 --> 00:28:44,224
We'll be able to get
close by the end, right?

451
00:28:44,613 --> 00:28:45,613
I wonder that, too.

452
00:28:45,638 --> 00:28:48,403
I don't really talk a lot when I
meet people for the first time.

453
00:28:48,856 --> 00:28:51,590
- I don't think that's true.
- You're pretty chatty.

454
00:28:51,615 --> 00:28:55,108
I sweated a lot.
My hands were all sweaty.

455
00:28:58,449 --> 00:29:00,369
- I feel like you're a good cook.
- Me?

456
00:29:00,394 --> 00:29:01,461
Yes. Am I wrong?

457
00:29:01,833 --> 00:29:05,826
- I feel like you enjoy it.
- I do, but I'm not that good at it.

458
00:29:05,851 --> 00:29:08,147
But people who enjoy
cooking are good at it.

459
00:29:08,837 --> 00:29:10,520
(The corners of his lips go up.)

460
00:29:11,176 --> 00:29:12,946
- Do you drink alcohol well?
- No.

461
00:29:12,971 --> 00:29:17,651
Two or three shots of soju
and I get red everywhere.

462
00:29:17,676 --> 00:29:19,743
Right. I get red up to my neck.

463
00:29:20,321 --> 00:29:23,773
What about you, Jae-hyung?
Oops, I'm sorry!

464
00:29:23,944 --> 00:29:26,072
- Do you two know each other?
- Do you know me?

465
00:29:26,797 --> 00:29:28,892
He looks like someone I know.

466
00:29:29,133 --> 00:29:33,839
As soon as I entered the room, I
thought, "He really looks like him."

467
00:29:33,864 --> 00:29:36,931
- That's why I naturally called
you by your name. - I see.

468
00:29:37,578 --> 00:29:38,645
All of a sudden?

469
00:29:38,802 --> 00:29:43,119
What if she did that on purpose?

470
00:29:43,973 --> 00:29:44,973
What if?

471
00:29:45,689 --> 00:29:46,949
(It's hot!)

472
00:29:47,405 --> 00:29:49,080
What are your hobbies?

473
00:29:49,814 --> 00:29:52,480
- I like bowling.
- Bowling?

474
00:29:53,170 --> 00:29:55,101
I was in the bowling team in middle school.

475
00:29:56,051 --> 00:29:57,584
I'm not good at it now.

476
00:29:57,979 --> 00:30:01,679
Same here. I used
to score 150 to 160.

477
00:30:01,704 --> 00:30:04,334
Wow, you're really good!

478
00:30:04,805 --> 00:30:07,058
My score is 130, and I thought I was good.

479
00:30:07,744 --> 00:30:10,030
- I think I'll score 100 now.
- I see.

480
00:30:10,725 --> 00:30:12,439
Anything else besides bowling?

481
00:30:12,464 --> 00:30:14,915
I love eating delicious food.

482
00:30:14,940 --> 00:30:16,839
- Going to hot spots?
- Everyone likes that.

483
00:30:17,339 --> 00:30:18,699
I love eating, too.

484
00:30:21,433 --> 00:30:26,878
- I recently went on a diet
because of that. - I see.

485
00:30:27,552 --> 00:30:29,655
- Do you like going for a drive?
- I love it.

486
00:30:29,680 --> 00:30:30,680
Really?

487
00:30:30,840 --> 00:30:34,453
- I love looking at the sky.
- I'm a cloud collector.

488
00:30:34,478 --> 00:30:36,646
I took a ton of pictures today.

489
00:30:37,720 --> 00:30:39,752
- The clouds are really pretty these days.
- Yeah.

490
00:30:39,777 --> 00:30:42,945
- The sky during the sunset is beautiful.
- It's pink.

491
00:30:42,970 --> 00:30:45,044
You get drenched in
those feelings for a moment.

492
00:30:45,452 --> 00:30:47,182
- They're really compatible.
- Yeah!

493
00:30:48,002 --> 00:30:49,835
Won-jae must feel a bit awkward.

494
00:30:51,800 --> 00:30:53,451
What time do you usually sleep?

495
00:30:53,476 --> 00:30:54,498
- Sleep?
- Yes.

496
00:30:54,523 --> 00:30:56,454
- I sleep before midnight.
- Same here.

497
00:30:56,479 --> 00:30:58,930
- Really?
- I tend to sleep early.

498
00:30:58,955 --> 00:31:01,331
- Do you wake up early, too?
- Around 7?

499
00:31:01,356 --> 00:31:05,047
I just got the chills! Me, too!

500
00:31:05,798 --> 00:31:07,877
- I don't have an alarm.
- Me neither.

501
00:31:07,902 --> 00:31:11,919
Right? This is scary.

502
00:31:12,600 --> 00:31:15,639
- What do you do when you wake up?
- I really love music.

503
00:31:15,664 --> 00:31:17,697
- Me, too.
- Really? What kind?

504
00:31:17,722 --> 00:31:19,855
I turn on the LP when I wake up.

505
00:31:20,591 --> 00:31:23,575
- I can't believe it.
- Wow, you must listen to music a lot.

506
00:31:23,889 --> 00:31:26,755
- I try collecting them.
- I'm so envious.

507
00:31:28,878 --> 00:31:30,282
Ji-min is in an awkward spot.

508
00:31:30,307 --> 00:31:33,627
- But aren't you taken aback by tomorrow?
- Yes.

509
00:31:33,652 --> 00:31:35,614
I can't believe we have to go back home.

510
00:31:35,639 --> 00:31:36,639
What do we do tomorrow?

511
00:31:38,777 --> 00:31:40,475
I have no idea what will happen.

512
00:31:40,500 --> 00:31:42,137
I'll feel pathetic if I get rejected.

513
00:31:42,712 --> 00:31:48,132
But on the other hand, no one
could pick up the girl.

514
00:31:48,157 --> 00:31:51,732
- That's possible if a girl gets
more than one votes. - Oh no.

515
00:31:52,133 --> 00:31:55,530
- What if I end up taking a cab there?
- Where do you live?

516
00:31:55,555 --> 00:31:57,969
- You said you live in Gwangjin-gu, right?
- Yes.

517
00:31:58,673 --> 00:32:01,473
(Will Jae-hyung go to
pick up Yeo-min tomorrow?)

518
00:32:01,498 --> 00:32:03,298
I'm worried about tomorrow.

519
00:32:03,723 --> 00:32:05,215
I think everyone is.

520
00:32:06,434 --> 00:32:08,941
I'll just have to assume
I'll be driving alone.

521
00:32:09,484 --> 00:32:11,992
- Just go to the lodging right away?
- Yeah, just be at ease.

522
00:32:12,017 --> 00:32:14,701
- I'll have the music on.
- There are five guys though.

523
00:32:14,726 --> 00:32:15,726
Right.

524
00:32:18,320 --> 00:32:21,453
But won't one of us come to pick you up?

525
00:32:22,356 --> 00:32:23,356
I think so.

526
00:32:25,006 --> 00:32:28,025
Then we'll both end up
not going. Just kidding!

527
00:32:28,958 --> 00:32:30,358
I'm pulling your leg.

528
00:32:31,603 --> 00:32:32,952
I think he'll go get her.

529
00:32:33,994 --> 00:32:35,947
Should we go? They
said we can go over there.

530
00:32:39,136 --> 00:32:40,738
(Ha-neul's gaze follows Su-won.)

531
00:32:40,763 --> 00:32:43,030
I think she's looking at him, too.

532
00:32:43,055 --> 00:32:45,258
They seem to be conscious of one another.

533
00:32:45,283 --> 00:32:47,697
- I think it'll be cold.
- I think it'll be cold.

534
00:32:48,843 --> 00:32:50,216
I get cold easily.

535
00:32:54,039 --> 00:32:56,475
- The breeze feels nice.
- It's gorgeous!

536
00:32:58,409 --> 00:33:00,809
- It's pretty.
- It's so beautiful!

537
00:33:01,136 --> 00:33:03,454
Is this Changdeokgung? What is that?

538
00:33:03,479 --> 00:33:05,050
- Isn't it Heunginjimun?
- Heunginjimun?

539
00:33:05,075 --> 00:33:07,233
- Yes. - I see. I didn't know.

540
00:33:07,608 --> 00:33:09,100
Where in Busan did you live?

541
00:33:09,125 --> 00:33:10,461
Jingoo. Gaya.

542
00:33:10,762 --> 00:33:11,762
I live in Seoul.

543
00:33:15,465 --> 00:33:18,173
(Just then, Yeo-min bumps into
the fence and spills her drink.)

544
00:33:18,439 --> 00:33:22,351
- It was too windy.
- I just have to wipe this.

545
00:33:26,002 --> 00:33:28,414
- How's the weather outside?
- It's...

546
00:33:28,439 --> 00:33:31,203
- Where's the restroom?
- I made a mess on the first day.

547
00:33:33,968 --> 00:33:37,263
He seems like he doesn't care, but...

548
00:33:41,599 --> 00:33:45,860
I think I was able to figure her out a bit.

549
00:33:46,183 --> 00:33:52,008
I'll keep observing her and try to
get her to like me on the second day.

550
00:33:52,364 --> 00:33:53,364
I'm confident.

551
00:33:53,672 --> 00:33:56,572
But the more I see
Jae-hyung, the more I trust him.

552
00:33:56,597 --> 00:33:58,664
- Oh, really?
- He's charming.

553
00:33:58,982 --> 00:34:02,267
- If you think about it, he's
very innocent. - Right.

554
00:34:02,292 --> 00:34:04,215
I think what he said will happen.

555
00:34:10,817 --> 00:34:11,817
(Glance)

556
00:34:12,086 --> 00:34:15,000
May I sit here?

557
00:34:15,791 --> 00:34:16,791
Of course.

558
00:34:20,345 --> 00:34:23,210
- Were you the second to arrive?
- The third.

559
00:34:24,286 --> 00:34:25,897
It must have been very awkward.

560
00:34:26,158 --> 00:34:27,358
Tell me about it.

561
00:34:28,204 --> 00:34:32,093
But I saw you try your
best, and I was grateful.

562
00:34:32,118 --> 00:34:33,172
I tried.

563
00:34:33,197 --> 00:34:36,757
I had no idea what to do, so I
kept touching my glass of water.

564
00:34:36,782 --> 00:34:39,553
But you made a lot of effort, too.

565
00:34:40,367 --> 00:34:44,494
I think everyone's nice here.
Both the men and women.

566
00:34:45,436 --> 00:34:47,253
I think you're really young.

567
00:34:47,753 --> 00:34:50,951
Really? I'm not. I'm not that young.

568
00:34:51,370 --> 00:34:52,370
Really?

569
00:34:53,790 --> 00:34:57,707
(Their ages and jobs are under wraps.)

570
00:34:59,377 --> 00:35:02,091
Is everyone sitting here again?

571
00:35:02,116 --> 00:35:03,706
- Oh, your double eyelids!
- Me?

572
00:35:03,731 --> 00:35:05,494
Is it past midnight, by any chance?

573
00:35:05,821 --> 00:35:06,965
I'm not sure.

574
00:35:09,361 --> 00:35:11,953
(Su-won, who was away
for a bit, comes back inside.)

575
00:35:12,512 --> 00:35:15,131
- Are we back at the bar now?
- Yes.

576
00:35:19,622 --> 00:35:22,274
- Did you guys talk a lot over there?
- Yes, we did.

577
00:35:22,990 --> 00:35:25,157
It's an hour and a half past my bedtime.

578
00:35:25,182 --> 00:35:27,883
- Please tell me if my double
eyelids appear. - Let me see.

579
00:35:28,251 --> 00:35:29,251
They're here.

580
00:35:31,179 --> 00:35:32,179
They're here.

581
00:35:33,662 --> 00:35:35,836
Oh my god. They're very noticeable.

582
00:35:36,490 --> 00:35:37,823
I look greasy, right?

583
00:35:37,848 --> 00:35:39,855
(He can't stop looking
at Ha-neul and Ji-min.)

584
00:35:40,534 --> 00:35:41,883
Let's not bully each other.

585
00:35:43,945 --> 00:35:47,243
(The two are getting along very well.)

586
00:35:49,837 --> 00:35:52,249
- Su-won can't hide his emotions.
- Oh no.

587
00:35:54,080 --> 00:36:00,881
Regarding first impressions,
I had my eyes on Ha-neul.

588
00:36:01,214 --> 00:36:05,064
She has big eyes and a
sharp and high-bridge nose.

589
00:36:05,842 --> 00:36:07,249
So I think she's all right.

590
00:36:07,786 --> 00:36:11,974
If she's interested in
me, too, I dare predict

591
00:36:11,999 --> 00:36:15,563
that we'll get into
a good relationship.

592
00:36:17,311 --> 00:36:18,707
He seems like a Love Catcher.

593
00:36:19,607 --> 00:36:21,797
- Right.
- He seems like a Love Catcher.

594
00:36:26,393 --> 00:36:28,734
- I was amazed that we have the same name.
- Me, too.

595
00:36:28,759 --> 00:36:30,641
Can you tell me the keyword? I'm curious.

596
00:36:31,024 --> 00:36:35,516
Ji-min seems really proactive.
He goes to different places.

597
00:36:35,815 --> 00:36:38,481
I feel like he's a Money Catcher.

598
00:36:38,506 --> 00:36:40,602
So if they're proactive,
they're Money Catchers?

599
00:36:42,489 --> 00:36:44,631
Can you tell me the keyword? I'm curious.

600
00:36:44,656 --> 00:36:46,927
- Do you remember a keyword?
- Me?

601
00:36:46,952 --> 00:36:49,247
Out of the women's keywords.

602
00:36:49,942 --> 00:36:54,555
The one that shocked me the most was "21."

603
00:36:54,880 --> 00:36:56,896
I think I know who that is.

604
00:36:58,624 --> 00:36:59,981
- I won't ask you.
- Okay.

605
00:37:00,006 --> 00:37:06,769
You look young, Ji-min, so I thought
that was you, but you don't act 21 at all.

606
00:37:06,794 --> 00:37:08,990
- Right?
- You seem thrilled.

607
00:37:09,015 --> 00:37:12,024
What? That's because you said I look young.

608
00:37:12,049 --> 00:37:13,646
You really do look very young.

609
00:37:15,103 --> 00:37:18,888
- I don't think she's 21.
- I think she is.

610
00:37:19,893 --> 00:37:21,694
What do you usually see in women?

611
00:37:22,420 --> 00:37:27,674
Honestly, I rely a lot on
first impressions and destiny.

612
00:37:29,260 --> 00:37:30,260
What about you?

613
00:37:34,535 --> 00:37:36,916
(The two men are waiting for her answer.)

614
00:37:36,941 --> 00:37:39,761
Someone you can peg as
nice the moment they speak.

615
00:37:42,338 --> 00:37:44,020
I'm trying to remember what I said.

616
00:37:46,032 --> 00:37:50,501
I'm curious if everyone
already has eyes for someone.

617
00:37:51,276 --> 00:37:53,236
I'm sure some of them do.

618
00:37:53,507 --> 00:37:55,974
- I do, too.
- Really?

619
00:37:56,377 --> 00:37:58,075
There's someone I'm curious about.

620
00:37:58,776 --> 00:38:00,043
I wonder who it is.

621
00:38:00,744 --> 00:38:01,744
Who is it?

622
00:38:03,519 --> 00:38:05,908
What about you?

623
00:38:09,493 --> 00:38:12,360
(She looks at the men at the other tables.)

624
00:38:13,577 --> 00:38:17,259
- Hello.
- Hello.

625
00:38:17,557 --> 00:38:21,287
- I'm Yang Ji-min.
- I'm Ahn Ji-min.

626
00:38:21,617 --> 00:38:23,719
- You two seem to have the same name.
- We do.

627
00:38:24,613 --> 00:38:27,875
I had eyes on him from the
first time I entered the room.

628
00:38:30,643 --> 00:38:33,358
I like people who seem like
they grew up with a lot of love.

629
00:38:33,383 --> 00:38:36,407
That's important for me, too.
I think you grew up with a lot of love.

630
00:38:36,928 --> 00:38:39,483
Really? I'm glad. I was totally adored.

631
00:38:42,831 --> 00:38:47,823
I think Ji-min's ideal
type is my ideal type.

632
00:38:47,848 --> 00:38:51,834
He likes people who
are kind and considerate.

633
00:38:52,904 --> 00:38:54,515
- Really?
- For real?

634
00:38:55,732 --> 00:38:58,517
There's someone I'm curious about.
What about you?

635
00:39:00,853 --> 00:39:03,945
(Ji-min looks elsewhere in
case he notices how she feels.)

636
00:39:04,122 --> 00:39:06,471
Why are you looking over there?
I guess it's not one of us.

637
00:39:08,006 --> 00:39:12,049
There is someone I want to have a
conversation in the car tomorrow morning.

638
00:39:12,677 --> 00:39:14,956
(She can't meet his eyes.)

639
00:39:15,782 --> 00:39:17,483
(Ba-thump, Ba-thump!)

640
00:39:17,508 --> 00:39:22,255
- My heart is fluttering!
- Will he be able to notice it?

641
00:39:22,952 --> 00:39:24,674
I think so.

642
00:39:24,716 --> 00:39:31,018
But she looked somewhere else,
so I don't think Ji-min figured it out.

643
00:39:31,357 --> 00:39:34,064
I wouldn't have been able to notice it.

644
00:39:34,179 --> 00:39:35,639
She looked way over there.

645
00:39:35,664 --> 00:39:39,490
But Ha-neul and Ji-min hit it off, too.

646
00:39:39,515 --> 00:39:42,390
They giggled together.

647
00:39:46,925 --> 00:39:50,428
- Su-won will definitely
go to Ha-neul, right? - Absolutely.

648
00:39:50,783 --> 00:39:53,910
- He could go there tonight.
- He might get a head start.

649
00:39:53,935 --> 00:39:56,246
He can't hide his emotions.

650
00:39:56,271 --> 00:39:59,607
He's definitely a Love
Catcher, and he's into Ha-neul.

651
00:39:59,632 --> 00:40:00,632
Totally.

652
00:40:00,657 --> 00:40:03,924
Tomorrow, the guys will
have to escort the girls.

653
00:40:03,949 --> 00:40:07,368
- Can you guess who will go to who?
- Ji-min will go to Ji-min.

654
00:40:08,230 --> 00:40:10,468
I think he'll go to Ha-neul.

655
00:40:11,377 --> 00:40:17,527
The way he was with her was a bit
different from how he was with Ji-min.

656
00:40:18,774 --> 00:40:25,228
I feel like he was vibing with her as a
friend and not as someone he could date.

657
00:40:25,253 --> 00:40:28,836
- So they're more like friends?
- Yes. They looked comfortable.

658
00:40:28,861 --> 00:40:32,769
Jae-hyung will go to Yeo-min.

659
00:40:32,794 --> 00:40:37,145
- Anyway, I hope it goes as he plans.
- I want to root for him.

660
00:40:37,170 --> 00:40:39,895
- They probably didn't get any sleep.
- Of course they didn't!

661
00:40:42,262 --> 00:40:45,569
(With the excitement of their first
meeting, the nine of them went home.)

662
00:40:47,673 --> 00:40:50,067
(The morning where their
second meeting will occur

663
00:40:53,951 --> 00:40:54,951
They're leaving.

664
00:40:57,079 --> 00:40:58,079
Hello.

665
00:41:00,952 --> 00:41:02,649
I'm the only one in a cab.

666
00:41:04,261 --> 00:41:05,596
I regret not buying a car.

667
00:41:06,982 --> 00:41:08,751
Coming together is what's important.

668
00:41:10,158 --> 00:41:12,596
(Where are the men's
hearts heading towards?)

669
00:41:16,167 --> 00:41:17,900
Wow, there Jae-hyung goes.

670
00:41:20,051 --> 00:41:21,582
It's the first date.

671
00:41:22,323 --> 00:41:24,964
I haven't decided
between them two, and I

672
00:41:25,170 --> 00:41:27,849
think a date with either
of them will be fine.

673
00:41:29,276 --> 00:41:30,982
That's when it all begins.

674
00:41:35,092 --> 00:41:36,933
I think I could say
it's love at first sight.

675
00:41:36,958 --> 00:41:41,025
Even if she likes someone
else, I'll do my best to steal her.

676
00:41:41,630 --> 00:41:43,757
He's set on Ha-neul.

677
00:41:46,937 --> 00:41:51,643
The one who caught my
eye the most was Ha-neul.

678
00:41:54,368 --> 00:41:55,628
(That's unexpected!)

679
00:41:55,653 --> 00:41:56,653
Really?

680
00:41:57,195 --> 00:42:00,949
When I think about who matches
with me the most, it's Yeo-min.

681
00:42:01,231 --> 00:42:03,294
- You live in Gwangjin-gu, right?
- Yes.

682
00:42:03,319 --> 00:42:05,589
- I live in Nowon.
- That's close by.

683
00:42:05,621 --> 00:42:07,862
I work out a lot at
Jungnangcheon.

684
00:42:07,887 --> 00:42:11,237
I used to work out there, too.
I love jogging.

685
00:42:11,262 --> 00:42:12,262
Seriously?

686
00:42:15,763 --> 00:42:18,142
(The two of them are
heading to the same place.)

687
00:42:18,167 --> 00:42:20,075
She has good vibes.

688
00:42:20,553 --> 00:42:24,370
I think I'll go to the one
I want to talk with more.

689
00:42:26,438 --> 00:42:27,828
They're in the same neighborhood.

690
00:42:29,920 --> 00:42:34,110
I talked with Ji-min and In-seong the most.

691
00:42:34,806 --> 00:42:37,226
I remember them the most.

692
00:42:41,026 --> 00:42:44,170
(Will the five men be able to enter
Love Mansion with the woman they want?)

693
00:42:46,604 --> 00:42:50,318
It seems like two men are
aiming for the same woman.

694
00:42:50,343 --> 00:42:52,156
Yes, their interests are overlapping.

695
00:42:55,317 --> 00:42:57,597
(Yoon Jung-woo)

696
00:42:58,464 --> 00:43:00,703
(The second man arrives at the next place.)

697
00:43:07,562 --> 00:43:09,912
(Kang Won-jae)

698
00:43:10,390 --> 00:43:12,700
(And where are the
other men going to?)

699
00:43:16,366 --> 00:43:17,432
I'm almost here.

700
00:43:18,088 --> 00:43:19,533
It's right across that, right?

701
00:43:20,687 --> 00:43:22,599
What if there are many other cars?

702
00:43:24,025 --> 00:43:26,031
(These two picked different women.)

703
00:43:33,208 --> 00:43:36,075
Oh no! The background looks the same!

704
00:43:36,272 --> 00:43:37,782
(Covering her mouth)

705
00:43:41,518 --> 00:43:42,780
This is driving me nuts.

706
00:43:45,608 --> 00:43:48,094
- He's here?
- Oh no!

707
00:43:48,367 --> 00:43:49,970
Where is this? The lot's full.

708
00:43:51,125 --> 00:43:52,370
Aww, man.

709
00:43:56,350 --> 00:43:57,350
Hello.

710
00:43:59,003 --> 00:44:00,710
Oh my god!

711
00:44:02,540 --> 00:44:03,969
Why did you come here?

712
00:44:06,741 --> 00:44:09,495
- I guess we connected.
- Yeah.

713
00:44:11,683 --> 00:44:14,874
- I think they're here for Ji-min.
- This is like a drama.

714
00:44:15,669 --> 00:44:18,441
(The other two cars
come to different locations.)

715
00:44:20,906 --> 00:44:23,041
I wonder who else came.

716
00:44:24,434 --> 00:44:25,434
(Glance)

717
00:44:29,338 --> 00:44:31,877
- The lot's full here, too.
- Good grief!

718
00:44:32,904 --> 00:44:35,103
(Oh no!)

719
00:44:36,432 --> 00:44:38,273
Won-jae and Jae-hyung.

720
00:44:42,441 --> 00:44:45,174
(They're not pleased with the situation.)

721
00:44:46,308 --> 00:44:48,908
I saw the Porsche and
got a bit disheartened.

722
00:44:50,882 --> 00:44:52,392
I thought it's worth trying.

723
00:44:54,659 --> 00:44:56,896
The war of nerves is tense here.

724
00:45:02,277 --> 00:45:05,039
I hope at least one person is here.
Or else, my pride will be hurt.

725
00:45:07,060 --> 00:45:10,592
Honestly, I thought at least
one person would come.

726
00:45:12,352 --> 00:45:15,153
What will I do if no one comes?

727
00:45:16,991 --> 00:45:20,935
I'm really worried that
no one will be here.

728
00:45:23,053 --> 00:45:27,442
I'm kind of interested in two guys.

729
00:45:29,227 --> 00:45:31,227
Su-won and Ji-min.

730
00:45:32,021 --> 00:45:33,409
I don't know.

731
00:45:34,370 --> 00:45:35,533
(Halt)

732
00:45:35,836 --> 00:45:38,987
Wait a minute. I don't think there
was anyone in the underground lot.

733
00:45:43,548 --> 00:45:44,629
(Synchronized)

734
00:45:44,724 --> 00:45:45,819
(Please!)

735
00:45:47,869 --> 00:45:51,869
(is the one waiting for her the
one she's been wishing for?)

736
00:45:52,122 --> 00:45:55,846
(Jung Su-won)

737
00:45:56,073 --> 00:45:57,683
Hello.

738
00:46:01,372 --> 00:46:03,483
Goodness! That's wonderful!

739
00:46:04,073 --> 00:46:06,398
- I hope they're both Love Catchers.
- Same here.

740
00:46:15,173 --> 00:46:17,902
- Hello.
- Hello.

741
00:46:18,381 --> 00:46:20,643
- Should I put your luggage in the trunk?
- Yes, please.

742
00:46:24,379 --> 00:46:25,379
Hello.

743
00:46:27,455 --> 00:46:28,709
- Wow.
- Did you sleep well?

744
00:46:28,734 --> 00:46:30,528
You didn't get enough sleep, right?

745
00:46:30,983 --> 00:46:32,880
Two hours? I think I
got two hours of sleep.

746
00:46:32,905 --> 00:46:35,142
- I slept for about three.
- It's hot, right?

747
00:46:35,167 --> 00:46:36,875
- No, it's cold.
- It is?

748
00:46:39,025 --> 00:46:41,555
(The second meeting of the
people with hot-and-cold chemistry)

749
00:46:42,773 --> 00:46:48,963
I connected with one person, and I
want to talk more with another person.

750
00:46:51,950 --> 00:46:53,394
I think it's that spot.

751
00:46:53,598 --> 00:46:56,919
(Two men are waiting for Yeo-min.)

752
00:46:58,816 --> 00:47:02,202
(Are they the escorts Yeo-min had in mind?)

753
00:47:06,949 --> 00:47:09,218
Goodness. Hello. Hello.

754
00:47:11,642 --> 00:47:12,761
What do I do?

755
00:47:14,529 --> 00:47:15,929
She has to choose.

756
00:47:16,998 --> 00:47:20,371
Will you get in my car?

757
00:47:21,368 --> 00:47:25,597
- Oh my gosh!
- Why is he doing that?

758
00:47:25,801 --> 00:47:26,801
What do we do?

759
00:47:28,015 --> 00:47:29,190
Will you get in my car?

760
00:47:32,097 --> 00:47:36,309
(Compared to the proactive Jae-hyung,
Won-jae has a dim expression.)

761
00:47:38,021 --> 00:47:40,449
What do I do?
What should I do?

762
00:47:41,405 --> 00:47:43,953
She feels bad for having to
choose right in front of them.

763
00:47:46,669 --> 00:47:47,669
I'll go with...

764
00:47:49,802 --> 00:47:53,420
- I'm not sure who she'll pick.
- She's in a pickle.

765
00:47:57,500 --> 00:48:00,900
- I'm sorry.
- It's fine.

766
00:48:00,925 --> 00:48:03,551
(Yeo-min chose Won-jae.)

767
00:48:05,562 --> 00:48:06,911
Oh no.

768
00:48:07,365 --> 00:48:11,488
(One man is happy
while the other is sad...)

769
00:48:12,041 --> 00:48:13,628
It's really heavy.

770
00:48:15,573 --> 00:48:17,321
(Is this part of his big picture, too...?)

771
00:48:17,346 --> 00:48:19,123
I wish this was part of his plan.

772
00:48:20,923 --> 00:48:22,288
- Hello.
- Hi.

773
00:48:23,121 --> 00:48:25,647
- Did you get some sleep?
- No.

774
00:48:25,785 --> 00:48:26,785
Me neither.

775
00:48:36,128 --> 00:48:37,794
This is driving me crazy.

776
00:48:46,728 --> 00:48:48,128
God, I'm embarrassed.

777
00:48:53,124 --> 00:48:54,846
Ugh, I'm humiliated.

778
00:48:56,545 --> 00:48:58,156
I'm curious what will happen here, too.

779
00:48:59,765 --> 00:49:03,640
I hope Ji-min, the one I
talked with the most, is here.

780
00:49:06,083 --> 00:49:08,508
Between Ji-min and Jung-woo,

781
00:49:09,149 --> 00:49:12,149
the one I want to get to know more is...

782
00:49:12,953 --> 00:49:18,774
This means no one came to
pick up either In-seong or Ji-min.

783
00:49:21,752 --> 00:49:25,085
(The one who disarmed
these two tense men are...?)

784
00:49:30,645 --> 00:49:32,217
In-seong!

785
00:49:35,081 --> 00:49:39,256
- Wow, what happened?
- This is unexpected.

786
00:49:40,571 --> 00:49:41,975
I never expected this.

787
00:49:42,574 --> 00:49:45,835
Is no one here? I don't
think anyone came.

788
00:49:47,110 --> 00:49:48,761
Oh no...

789
00:49:50,860 --> 00:49:52,407
Uh-oh...

790
00:49:53,751 --> 00:49:55,957
- Please choose comfortably.
- Okay.

791
00:49:57,354 --> 00:50:00,113
(In-seong can't avoid this
moment of decision either.)

792
00:50:01,369 --> 00:50:02,703
- Who is it?
- Who is it?

793
00:50:05,175 --> 00:50:07,556
- Jung-woo.
- She'll pick Ji-min.

794
00:50:08,608 --> 00:50:11,513
(Who is In-seong's heart leaning towards?)

795
00:50:11,865 --> 00:50:14,643
I'm sorry.

796
00:50:18,032 --> 00:50:21,165
- That's unfortunate.
- This is really bitter.

797
00:50:22,828 --> 00:50:23,947
It's heavy.

798
00:50:24,181 --> 00:50:28,053
- Should I put it in the back?
- Sure.

799
00:50:28,375 --> 00:50:30,692
- You can get in the car first.
- Thank you.

800
00:50:32,314 --> 00:50:33,703
(Stare)

801
00:50:35,576 --> 00:50:36,576
(Bow)

802
00:50:39,407 --> 00:50:43,404
(Is Ji-min not able to go because
he has lingering feelings for her?)

803
00:50:47,474 --> 00:50:50,407
Sir, I'm alone. You can
take me there alone.

804
00:50:55,157 --> 00:50:56,601
I can just go comfortably.

805
00:51:02,764 --> 00:51:05,245
(At the same time,
Ji-min's taxi arrives.)

806
00:51:05,270 --> 00:51:07,715
Hello, sir. I'm sorry,
but this luggage is

807
00:51:07,740 --> 00:51:10,526
really heavy. Can you
help me load it in the car?

808
00:51:12,701 --> 00:51:15,605
- On top of this, the luggage
is heavy, too. - Thank you.

809
00:51:16,553 --> 00:51:17,926
There's one more.

810
00:51:18,109 --> 00:51:20,005
This one is heavier.

811
00:51:20,334 --> 00:51:22,706
- Should I get it from the other side.
- No, just get in.

812
00:51:23,609 --> 00:51:26,323
Thank you, sir. Thank you.

813
00:51:30,541 --> 00:51:35,782
(They head towards Love Mansion.)

814
00:51:40,384 --> 00:51:44,716
(The seat beside him
feels strangely empty.)

815
00:51:48,109 --> 00:51:49,776
I should've bought a car.

816
00:51:51,866 --> 00:51:54,216
(Someone calls the upset Ji-min.)

817
00:51:54,241 --> 00:51:58,078
Hi, mom. I'm heading to the
lodging in a cab all by myself.

818
00:51:58,758 --> 00:52:00,575
I'm alone. The others are going in pairs.

819
00:52:02,452 --> 00:52:03,452
It's okay.

820
00:52:04,014 --> 00:52:05,531
- Did you get rejected?
- Yeah.

821
00:52:05,556 --> 00:52:08,653
It could be because she doesn't like me,

822
00:52:08,899 --> 00:52:13,232
but somehow, I'm disappointed
that I don't have a car.

823
00:52:13,257 --> 00:52:16,185
You didn't tell her you don't have
one because you don't need it?

824
00:52:16,210 --> 00:52:19,132
Mom, I didn't even have a
chance to explain that to her.

825
00:52:20,129 --> 00:52:26,671
I couldn't tell her why I didn't have a car
yet and about how I'm a realistic person.

826
00:52:27,010 --> 00:52:29,303
I'm just heading there by myself.

827
00:52:30,434 --> 00:52:31,767
I need to buy a car.

828
00:52:32,857 --> 00:52:35,643
I don't have a Porsche,
but I'll drive like this is one.

829
00:52:35,668 --> 00:52:37,399
- I don't really know cars.
- I see.

830
00:52:37,835 --> 00:52:38,835
It's fine.

831
00:52:40,352 --> 00:52:42,686
I felt like we have similar tastes.

832
00:52:43,002 --> 00:52:47,010
I thought you felt the same way,
so I kind of anticipated you coming.

833
00:52:47,156 --> 00:52:49,823
- Really?
- Yes, I thought maybe you'd come.

834
00:52:50,256 --> 00:52:52,123
We didn't get to talk a lot.

835
00:52:53,151 --> 00:52:54,615
They look good together, too.

836
00:52:55,866 --> 00:52:57,681
(What about Jung-woo and In-seong?)

837
00:52:57,706 --> 00:52:59,930
- Thank you.
- For what?

838
00:53:00,418 --> 00:53:02,489
- For coming.
- Oh.

839
00:53:04,628 --> 00:53:05,628
Thank you.

840
00:53:07,629 --> 00:53:10,328
When I first met you,
what caught my eye were

841
00:53:10,353 --> 00:53:13,170
your glasses and that
ring on your pinky finger.

842
00:53:13,503 --> 00:53:16,351
- Your glasses look really good on you.
- They do?

843
00:53:17,999 --> 00:53:21,786
I brought another pair of glasses,
but I'll continue wearing these ones.

844
00:53:23,409 --> 00:53:25,297
- For a week?
- Yes.

845
00:53:25,322 --> 00:53:27,530
(Whatever In-seong likes!)

846
00:53:28,056 --> 00:53:29,699
(The final couple: Su-won & Ha-neul)

847
00:53:31,601 --> 00:53:38,382
Can I ask you this? Whose first
impressions did you like yesterday?

848
00:53:39,261 --> 00:53:41,125
- You said there were two.
- Right.

849
00:53:41,612 --> 00:53:44,548
Is there someone you're interested in?

850
00:53:44,580 --> 00:53:47,059
- Yes.
- Really? What about you?

851
00:53:47,594 --> 00:53:49,127
Same here. Two of them.

852
00:53:50,979 --> 00:53:54,066
- Two for you, too?
- One for me.

853
00:53:57,438 --> 00:53:59,898
Is one of them here?

854
00:54:02,499 --> 00:54:03,697
(Flustered)

855
00:54:04,120 --> 00:54:05,826
Is he the one taking you there?

856
00:54:06,155 --> 00:54:08,924
Yes, he is.

857
00:54:08,949 --> 00:54:10,281
- He did?
- Yes.

858
00:54:11,634 --> 00:54:13,603
I see. Okay.

859
00:54:14,021 --> 00:54:17,955
They're both very straightforward.

860
00:54:18,365 --> 00:54:23,447
- Is the one you were talking about me?
- Yes, it's only one for me. You.

861
00:54:27,231 --> 00:54:29,167
- They look good together.
- Yes, they do.

862
00:54:30,988 --> 00:54:37,261
(Truth hidden within secrets and the youths
who have stepped forward to find love.)

863
00:54:42,103 --> 00:54:44,841
- Wow!
- That's really nice.

864
00:54:45,122 --> 00:54:46,837
There's a place like that in Seoul?

865
00:54:46,862 --> 00:54:49,007
(Love Mansion)

866
00:54:51,124 --> 00:54:54,994
(One cab arrives first.)

867
00:54:57,867 --> 00:54:58,867
Thank you.

868
00:55:05,602 --> 00:55:10,120
(First housemate: Ahn Ji-min)

869
00:55:11,602 --> 00:55:13,202
Wow, that's really nice.

870
00:55:14,307 --> 00:55:17,201
(What kind of story will
these nine youths make?)

871
00:55:33,736 --> 00:55:36,929
(He walks through the
door and sees the first area.)

872
00:55:40,137 --> 00:55:43,053
(Common dining room)

873
00:55:43,078 --> 00:55:45,612
I wonder what kind of
things will happen in here.

874
00:55:46,632 --> 00:55:48,108
Wow, I'm the first one here.

875
00:55:50,168 --> 00:55:53,867
(Ji-min's heart is covered
with frustration and emptiness.)

876
00:55:57,146 --> 00:56:01,977
(And one girl is shortening
the distance between them.)

877
00:56:03,874 --> 00:56:06,437
- Hello.
- Hello.

878
00:56:08,416 --> 00:56:09,869
- Are you alone?
- Yes.

879
00:56:09,894 --> 00:56:10,894
I see.

880
00:56:11,435 --> 00:56:13,324
- I think I'm the first one here.
- Really?

881
00:56:14,361 --> 00:56:15,591
Why are you so breathless?

882
00:56:15,854 --> 00:56:17,861
I rushed up here.

883
00:56:18,139 --> 00:56:20,284
- Did you run?
- Yes, because it's raining.

884
00:56:24,873 --> 00:56:27,214
We met yesterday, but it
feels like this is our first time.

885
00:56:27,239 --> 00:56:29,739
- Really? We didn't talk that much.
- Yeah.

886
00:56:30,553 --> 00:56:34,886
But because of the party
yesterday, it's not awkward.

887
00:56:36,909 --> 00:56:44,712
- I think since he's here alone,
she sees some kind of hope. - Of course!

888
00:56:48,999 --> 00:56:49,999
Is it here?

889
00:56:50,785 --> 00:56:51,785
Is it?

890
00:56:53,831 --> 00:56:55,211
I'm flustered.

891
00:56:56,286 --> 00:56:57,818
Love Mansion.

892
00:57:01,045 --> 00:57:02,045
Come in.

893
00:57:02,904 --> 00:57:04,380
Did he drop the honorifics?

894
00:57:05,589 --> 00:57:08,487
- They're coming together.
- I guess they came together.

895
00:57:12,208 --> 00:57:17,920
- Hello.
- Hello.

896
00:57:18,539 --> 00:57:20,205
- It's really nice.
- Yeah.

897
00:57:21,263 --> 00:57:24,606
- Do I sit here? Can I sit here?
- When did you get here?

898
00:57:24,758 --> 00:57:27,299
- More than ten minutes ago.
- Really?

899
00:57:32,864 --> 00:57:38,071
I think it's great that we
didn't have to come here alone.

900
00:57:38,869 --> 00:57:42,464
- Right. What a relief. - I was
worried that I'd have to come by myself.

901
00:57:44,184 --> 00:57:45,335
It's good.

902
00:57:46,429 --> 00:57:48,903
Oh, he thinks they came together!

903
00:57:48,928 --> 00:57:52,825
Because they were here first?
Oh my goodness.

904
00:57:53,775 --> 00:57:56,592
What did you guys do?
Did you just come here right away?

905
00:57:56,617 --> 00:57:59,198
It took more than an hour to get here.

906
00:57:59,368 --> 00:58:01,074
You had a conversation for an hour?

907
00:58:01,099 --> 00:58:03,003
It wasn't too bad.

908
00:58:03,428 --> 00:58:04,428
(Shy)

909
00:58:04,453 --> 00:58:07,770
Ha-neul is really down-to-earth, so I
think it'd be comfortable to be around her.

910
00:58:11,714 --> 00:58:12,714
Yes, well...

911
00:58:15,368 --> 00:58:17,154
For some reason,
there's tension...

912
00:58:20,340 --> 00:58:22,023
- This must be it.
- Yes.

913
00:58:23,423 --> 00:58:25,956
- Hello.
- Hello.

914
00:58:27,255 --> 00:58:30,453
- Hello.
- Hello.

915
00:58:30,478 --> 00:58:34,154
(An uncomfortable love triangle
surrounding a man who wasn't chosen.)

916
00:58:38,074 --> 00:58:40,677
In-seong feels bad.

917
00:58:44,866 --> 00:58:47,066
(Feeling awkward for some reason)

918
00:58:49,507 --> 00:58:52,055
(Another man is unfamiliar
with this situation.)

919
00:58:52,336 --> 00:58:55,288
Gosh, I'm losing my mind here.

920
00:58:56,239 --> 00:58:59,834
Did he laugh all the way here?

921
00:59:00,198 --> 00:59:02,907
(Fifth housemate: Seo Jae-hyung)

922
00:59:04,334 --> 00:59:06,301
He's trudging.

923
00:59:08,058 --> 00:59:11,851
"Love Mission."

924
00:59:13,470 --> 00:59:16,271
- Oh dear.
- He must be having a rough time.

925
00:59:16,296 --> 00:59:17,980
Of course. He's in no right mind.

926
00:59:20,709 --> 00:59:23,049
- Hello.
- Hello.

927
00:59:24,192 --> 00:59:26,208
- You're all here.
- Yes.

928
00:59:32,022 --> 00:59:34,752
- You look a bit brighter than yesterday.
- I do?

929
00:59:34,777 --> 00:59:35,777
Yes.

930
00:59:36,246 --> 00:59:37,889
You seem more at ease.

931
00:59:38,818 --> 00:59:40,844
I kind of got adjusted to everything.

932
00:59:44,256 --> 00:59:45,820
You have so much luggage.

933
00:59:46,766 --> 00:59:48,566
How did you bring all this?

934
00:59:49,841 --> 00:59:52,269
- I love things like this.
- You do?

935
00:59:52,294 --> 00:59:56,234
Yes. I absolutely love
things like gardens and parks.

936
00:59:57,196 --> 01:00:00,635
- I love grass.
- You must really like it here.

937
01:00:00,660 --> 01:00:02,226
Yes, I love it.

938
01:00:03,020 --> 01:00:04,934
They seem to have gotten a lot closer.

939
01:00:08,020 --> 01:00:15,721
- Hello.
- Hello.

940
01:00:18,849 --> 01:00:21,484
- It's really nice.
- Right?

941
01:00:21,509 --> 01:00:24,208
I love how there's so much grass.
I love grass.

942
01:00:26,309 --> 01:00:27,801
It's like a forest.

943
01:00:28,476 --> 01:00:29,864
(Peek)

944
01:00:34,594 --> 01:00:36,817
(All nine participants have
entered Love Mansion.)

945
01:00:37,414 --> 01:00:39,939
Oh my god!

946
01:00:40,121 --> 01:00:42,497
- I knew this would happen.
- That scared me!

947
01:00:42,620 --> 01:00:44,214
- Oh my.
- Wow.

948
01:00:45,441 --> 01:00:46,631
Amazing.

949
01:00:47,012 --> 01:00:51,172
- Finally!
- I'm nervous. Why am I so nervous?

950
01:00:52,335 --> 01:00:54,018
It has finally come.

951
01:00:55,049 --> 01:00:58,243
(You will have seven
days to find true love.)

952
01:00:58,268 --> 01:00:59,421
Oh, a week.

953
01:01:03,588 --> 01:01:05,352
(Couples who win the
couple challenges get

954
01:01:05,377 --> 01:01:07,262
enter the "Night Date"
or "Room of Secrets.")

955
01:01:09,052 --> 01:01:10,742
It must be a date at night.

956
01:01:10,767 --> 01:01:12,300
It says "or."

957
01:01:12,859 --> 01:01:14,393
I guess you can choose.

958
01:01:14,701 --> 01:01:17,224
Oh, you can choose.

959
01:01:18,261 --> 01:01:21,387
(You can express your
interest only once per day.)

960
01:01:21,514 --> 01:01:23,072
How do you do that?

961
01:01:23,097 --> 01:01:26,552
So once a day, whenever
they want, they can put their

962
01:01:26,577 --> 01:01:29,904
coin in the locker of the
one they're interested in.

963
01:01:29,929 --> 01:01:31,968
If they change their
mind, they'll take it

964
01:01:31,993 --> 01:01:33,822
out and put it in a
different locker, right?

965
01:01:33,847 --> 01:01:35,499
Right. They'll put it somewhere else.

966
01:01:35,524 --> 01:01:39,575
Then those who try to express
their feelings late at night may see

967
01:01:39,600 --> 01:01:43,331
someone else's coin already in
that box when they open that door.

968
01:01:43,356 --> 01:01:46,485
Right. So you have to do it very carefully.

969
01:01:48,574 --> 01:01:51,873
(On the last day, the final selections and
everyone's identities will be unveiled.)

970
01:01:51,898 --> 01:01:56,676
(On the last day, the final selections and
everyone's identities will be unveiled.)

971
01:01:57,410 --> 01:01:59,666
(Another message appears after that.)

972
01:02:00,314 --> 01:02:03,526
(Please introduce yourself.)

973
01:02:04,563 --> 01:02:10,271
That means the Money Catchers can introduce
themselves as their fake identities. Right?

974
01:02:11,663 --> 01:02:14,490
- So we have to introduce ourselves.
- I knew this would happen.

975
01:02:15,297 --> 01:02:16,297
I'm shaking.

976
01:02:16,726 --> 01:02:17,987
I'm curious.

977
01:02:20,152 --> 01:02:21,525
You can go first.

978
01:02:21,977 --> 01:02:23,413
I'm...

979
01:02:26,206 --> 01:02:27,872
32 years old.

980
01:02:28,809 --> 01:02:33,098
I'm working as a freelance
travel writer right now.

981
01:02:35,255 --> 01:02:36,961
I remember that profile.

982
01:02:39,735 --> 01:02:41,291
I'm 30 years old.

983
01:02:42,188 --> 01:02:45,912
And I'm working at a company in Pangyo.

984
01:02:47,450 --> 01:02:49,268
- You're 30?
- Do I look older?

985
01:02:49,833 --> 01:02:51,961
No! Why would you say that?

986
01:02:53,183 --> 01:02:55,654
- Ji-min is him! - The ambassador
of Sungkyunkwan University.

987
01:02:55,679 --> 01:02:58,220
- The face of Sungkyunkwan University.
- An elite.

988
01:02:59,690 --> 01:03:07,674
I'm 29 years old, and I'm a researcher
of the LG Electronics development team.

989
01:03:08,640 --> 01:03:10,076
I told you I'm from Busan.

990
01:03:10,101 --> 01:03:14,553
That's my hometown, and
my workplace is in Changwon.

991
01:03:15,351 --> 01:03:17,884
So I'm going back and forth.

992
01:03:18,567 --> 01:03:20,680
Oh, he's the male god of
an engineering university.

993
01:03:26,444 --> 01:03:28,261
I have a lot of jobs.

994
01:03:30,833 --> 01:03:34,846
I'm in real estate, and I'm
the owner of a fashion brand.

995
01:03:35,740 --> 01:03:40,430
Also, I have two cafe franchises.

996
01:03:41,395 --> 01:03:44,078
- How old are you?
- I'm 32.

997
01:03:46,052 --> 01:03:48,496
- You two are the same age.
- Let's be friends.

998
01:03:51,144 --> 01:03:53,509
There's quite a gap with my age.

999
01:03:54,252 --> 01:03:55,847
(Hesitate)

1000
01:03:56,196 --> 01:03:58,214
You can say it comfortably.

1001
01:03:59,053 --> 01:04:01,750
My name is Kang Won-jae,
and I'm 23 years old.

1002
01:04:01,775 --> 01:04:04,719
I'm a college student
majoring in physical education.

1003
01:04:04,946 --> 01:04:07,438
I was in "Steel Troops."

1004
01:04:07,463 --> 01:04:09,271
- Huh?
- You were?

1005
01:04:09,656 --> 01:04:13,981
- Which team were you in?
- I was the youngest member of SDT.

1006
01:04:14,241 --> 01:04:16,121
No wonder he looked familiar!

1007
01:04:16,919 --> 01:04:19,523
- You're really observant.
- I loved that show.

1008
01:04:21,405 --> 01:04:22,405
Wow.

1009
01:04:22,971 --> 01:04:27,170
I'm 26 years old, and I'm a dance teacher.

1010
01:04:29,241 --> 01:04:33,280
- That job suits you.
- Thanks.

1011
01:04:34,372 --> 01:04:35,372
I'm...

1012
01:04:37,686 --> 01:04:39,583
27 years old,

1013
01:04:40,380 --> 01:04:45,165
and I recently opened a restaurant.

1014
01:04:47,076 --> 01:04:49,068
What? Then you're good at cooking!

1015
01:04:49,333 --> 01:04:53,183
- I'm not the one who cooks.
- She's very shy.

1016
01:04:53,208 --> 01:04:56,107
She's the boss, not the chef.

1017
01:04:56,961 --> 01:04:59,072
I'm 21 years old.

1018
01:04:59,097 --> 01:05:00,421
- That was you?
- Yes.

1019
01:05:01,914 --> 01:05:06,355
I'm a college student
studying aviation tourism.

1020
01:05:06,380 --> 01:05:09,406
I'm trying to become a flight attendant.

1021
01:05:09,431 --> 01:05:10,764
It really suits you.

1022
01:05:11,603 --> 01:05:12,603
Thank you.

1023
01:05:12,856 --> 01:05:14,737
She's really 21.

1024
01:05:15,417 --> 01:05:19,774
I'm 26 years old, and I'm currently
studying at a university in California.

1025
01:05:20,685 --> 01:05:24,326
- So you're taking a break from school?
- It's all online classes now.

1026
01:05:24,351 --> 01:05:26,307
Yes, because of COVID-19.

1027
01:05:26,426 --> 01:05:28,651
- No wonder you have great pronunciation.
- Yeah.

1028
01:05:31,788 --> 01:05:33,608
You know suspenders...

1029
01:05:33,633 --> 01:05:37,142
(Is her English a habit? Or is she
purposely doing this to fool everyone?)

1030
01:05:37,167 --> 01:05:40,567
I knew it when I heard you
say a few English words.

1031
01:05:41,237 --> 01:05:44,721
- Who's the one with a franchise?
- The franchise?

1032
01:05:44,962 --> 01:05:46,755
- Here.
- Me.

1033
01:05:47,371 --> 01:05:50,323
- I thought it's unique.
- Yes, I remember it.

1034
01:05:50,613 --> 01:05:53,850
I built the building myself, and
I'm living at the very top floor.

1035
01:05:53,875 --> 01:05:57,973
The first floor is where the cafe is,
and the middle floor is for new residents.

1036
01:05:58,612 --> 01:06:01,566
- Do you make the coffee yourself?
- The employees do that.

1037
01:06:02,490 --> 01:06:05,514
Both of you are owners but
don't get involved in the work.

1038
01:06:05,539 --> 01:06:06,667
But at least you cook.

1039
01:06:06,692 --> 01:06:09,907
I have a few branches,
so I can't do it all myself.

1040
01:06:10,395 --> 01:06:13,966
There's one in Incheon and somewhere else.

1041
01:06:13,991 --> 01:06:17,279
And I have a fashion brand, too.

1042
01:06:17,304 --> 01:06:18,904
You're truly incredible.

1043
01:06:19,052 --> 01:06:20,727
I worked hard.

1044
01:06:22,432 --> 01:06:25,185
I had no idea you were 21.

1045
01:06:25,533 --> 01:06:28,291
Really? Who did you think was 21 then?

1046
01:06:28,316 --> 01:06:32,263
Let's talk about that now. Who did
you think was who based on the profiles?

1047
01:06:32,288 --> 01:06:36,069
- I think it will be interesting.
- Who did you think was 21?

1048
01:06:36,094 --> 01:06:38,239
I think I made a mistake.

1049
01:06:40,707 --> 01:06:44,173
(What's on Ji-min's mind?)

1050
01:06:44,780 --> 01:06:49,097
Ha-neul? I think she's 21.

1051
01:06:50,707 --> 01:06:52,651
I thought she was 21, too.

1052
01:06:56,087 --> 01:06:58,354
She's very beautiful and graceful,

1053
01:07:00,599 --> 01:07:02,799
but I felt like she's very young.

1054
01:07:03,682 --> 01:07:08,221
I tend to draw a line if I
think someone's too young.

1055
01:07:09,665 --> 01:07:11,132
I don't think I saw...

1056
01:07:13,417 --> 01:07:15,769
her as a woman.

1057
01:07:17,554 --> 01:07:23,006
I'm 27 years old.

1058
01:07:24,800 --> 01:07:28,466
- I love looking at the sky.
- I'm a cloud collector.

1059
01:07:28,498 --> 01:07:31,525
I took so many photos today, too!

1060
01:07:32,419 --> 01:07:34,307
That's right. They really got along.

1061
01:07:34,763 --> 01:07:37,795
He thought she was young
and drew a line between them.

1062
01:07:38,815 --> 01:07:40,592
I think I made a mistake.

1063
01:07:43,335 --> 01:07:45,858
Their interests may completely
change after the introductions!

1064
01:07:47,188 --> 01:07:49,346
I have no idea what he's thinking.

1065
01:07:54,741 --> 01:07:58,764
(The day before the final selection)

1066
01:08:02,794 --> 01:08:04,501
- What's going on?
- Who are they?

1067
01:08:06,101 --> 01:08:07,792
- Ji-min and...
- What's happening?

1068
01:08:09,112 --> 01:08:10,112
Su-won.

1069
01:08:11,338 --> 01:08:12,996
- What's wrong?
- And Ha-neul!

1070
01:08:13,179 --> 01:08:14,981
Things are serious.

1071
01:08:20,466 --> 01:08:22,307
Did they fight?

1072
01:08:32,034 --> 01:08:33,835
I'm gonna say it now since he's not here.

1073
01:08:37,945 --> 01:08:39,357
I think he was interested in you.

1074
01:08:41,933 --> 01:08:44,901
I feel like Ji-min was into you.

1075
01:08:53,096 --> 01:08:54,334
And you...

1076
01:08:57,350 --> 01:08:59,449
probably have some feelings for him, too.

1077
01:09:01,947 --> 01:09:03,756
You know you were selfish, too.

1078
01:09:13,416 --> 01:09:20,199
(It was a tsunami of an
unfathomable and uncontrollable scale.)

1079
01:09:20,224 --> 01:09:21,224
Why was he selfish?

1080
01:09:22,315 --> 01:09:23,715
Why did she say that?

1081
01:09:35,911 --> 01:09:37,445
I'm getting pissed off.

1082
01:09:38,538 --> 01:09:40,404
Why did things turn out like this?

1083
01:09:40,860 --> 01:09:43,956
- What's going on?
- Was he interested in someone else?

1084
01:09:45,215 --> 01:09:46,278
What's happening?

1085
01:09:46,303 --> 01:09:48,906
- This is it, right?
- That's the end?

1086
01:09:49,004 --> 01:09:51,218
You expect us to go
home like this? We can't!

1087
01:09:52,258 --> 01:09:55,635
- Wouldn't that be horrible?
- If you could just show us a bit more...

1088
01:09:55,896 --> 01:09:59,002
Just 30 seconds, please.
I won't ask for more.

1089
01:09:59,027 --> 01:10:02,125
Please do this for us.
Or at least give us soju.

1090
01:10:02,150 --> 01:10:03,883
I can't go home like this.

1091
01:10:08,501 --> 01:10:10,771
Prepare a dish for a date?

1092
01:10:12,108 --> 01:10:13,774
Are we each choosing one?

1093
01:10:14,353 --> 01:10:17,283
I thought of Su-won,
but I thought there

1094
01:10:17,308 --> 01:10:20,667
wouldn't enough time
to get to know the others.

1095
01:10:21,308 --> 01:10:24,585
I want to talk with someone else, too.

1096
01:10:25,233 --> 01:10:28,439
It's our first time, so it's not
bad to get to know others.

1097
01:10:29,855 --> 01:10:31,324
This is driving me nuts.

1098
01:10:31,349 --> 01:10:33,311
I feel like I'll be full
even if I don't eat.

1099
01:10:34,544 --> 01:10:37,917
I felt emotions I've
never experienced before.

1100
01:10:39,065 --> 01:10:43,025
Rather than feeling
interest, it was really warm.

1101
01:10:43,243 --> 01:10:46,275
It was warm food.

1102
01:10:46,595 --> 01:10:49,169
I thought at least one
woman would come to me.

1103
01:10:50,316 --> 01:10:53,197
I feel like the third wheel.

1104
01:10:53,890 --> 01:10:56,493
I can't intervene in their
conversation. It's hard.

1105
01:10:58,427 --> 01:10:59,840
She's here!

1106
01:10:59,929 --> 01:11:01,214
I got goosebumps!

1107
01:11:01,239 --> 01:11:03,986
This is what it's supposed to be like.
She's here now.

1108
01:11:05,013 --> 01:11:07,080
There were more men than women.

1109
01:11:07,787 --> 01:11:11,207
- I got a bit relaxed.
- I suddenly got happy.

1110
01:11:12,076 --> 01:11:13,743
- Hello.
- Hello.

1111
01:11:16,612 --> 01:11:19,906
Someone who's close
to my ideal type has appeared.

1112
01:11:20,315 --> 01:11:21,894
Her first impression wasn't bad.

1113
01:11:22,282 --> 01:11:25,354
- She's beautiful.
- It's the beginning.

1114
01:11:26,289 --> 01:11:28,224
My name is...
